{"title_page": "Diocese of S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland", "text_new": "{{Infobox diocese\n|jurisdiction = Diocese\n|name         = S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland\n|local        = S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland bisped\u00f8mme\n|image        = Bod\u00f8 domkirke.jpg \n|caption      = View of Bod\u00f8 Cathedral\n|country      = [[Norway]]\n|territory    = [[Nordland]]\n|denomination = [[Church of Norway]]\n|established  = 1952\n|bishop       = [[Ann-Helen Fjeldstad Jusnes]]\n|cathedral    = [[Bod\u00f8 Cathedral]]\n|deaneries    = Bod\u00f8 domprosti, Lofoten, Ofoten, Vester\u00e5len, Salten, Nord-Helgeland, Indre Helgeland, S\u00f8r-Helgeland\n|parishes     = 96\n|members      = 198,420\t\n|map          = Dioceses Church of Norway.svg\n|map_caption  = Location of S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland diocese\n|website      = http://www.kirken.no/sor-haalogaland\n|footnotes    = Reference<ref name=\"snl\">{{cite web|url=http://snl.no/S%C3%B8r-H%C3%A5logaland_bisped%C3%B8mme|title=S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland bisped\u00f8mme|author=Store norske leksikon|authorlink=Store norske leksikon|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2011-10-28}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland''' is a [[diocese]] in the [[Church of Norway]]. The Diocese covers the Lutheran [[Church of Norway]] churches located within [[Nordland]] county in [[Norway]].  The diocese is headquartered in the [[Bod\u00f8 (town)|town of Bod\u00f8]] at [[Bod\u00f8 Cathedral]], the seat of the presiding Bishop [[Ann-Helen Fjeldstad Jusnes]] (since 2015).  The diocese is divided into eight [[deanery|deaneries]] {{lang|no|(prosti)}}.\n\n==History==\nIn 1952, the old [[Diocese of H\u00e5logaland]] (which covered all of [[Northern Norway]]) was split into two: the Diocese of S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland (Nordland county) and the [[Diocese of Nord-H\u00e5logaland]] ([[Troms]], [[Finnmark]], and [[Svalbard]]).\n\n==Bishops==\nThe bishops of S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland since its creation in 1952:\n\n*1952\u20131959: [[Wollert Krohn-Hansen]] \n*1959\u20131969: [[Hans Edvard Wisl\u00f8ff]]\n*1969\u20131982: [[Bjarne Odd Weider]] \n*1982\u20131992: [[Fredrik Gr\u00f8nnings\u00e6ter]] \n*1992\u20132006: [[\u00d8ystein Ingar Larsen]] \n*2007-2015: [[Tor Berger J\u00f8rgensen]] \n*Since 2015: [[Ann-Helen Fjeldstad Jusnes]] \n\n==Cathedral==\n{{main|Bod\u00f8 Cathedral}}\nThe old church in Bod\u00f8 was destroyed during [[World War II]], and after the war plans were made to replace the church and make it the cathedral for the new diocese. The foundation stone was laid in 1954 and was consecrated by Bishop [[Wollert Krohn-Hansen]] in 1956. There is also a memorial to those who died in Bod\u00f8 during the [[Second World War]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ub.uit.no/baser/arkinord/categories.php?cat_id=180&l=norwegian|title=Bod\u00f8 Cathedral|publisher=Arkitekturguide Nordnorge og Svalbard}}</ref>\n\n==Structure==\nThe Diocese of S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland is divided into eight [[deanery|deaneries]] ({{lang-no|prosti}}).  Each one corresponds to several municipalities in the diocese. Each municipality is further divided into one or more [[parish]]es which each contain one or more congregations. See each municipality below for lists of churches and parishes within them.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Deanery (''prosti'') !! Municipalities !! Diocese Map\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Bod\u00f8_domprosti|'''Bod\u00f8 domprosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: lower blue)</small>||[[Bod\u00f8]], [[Gildesk\u00e5l]], [[Mel\u00f8y]], [[R\u00f8st]], [[V\u00e6r\u00f8y]]||rowspan=\"8\"|[[File:Prostier i Nordland.svg|200px]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Lofoten_prosti|'''Lofoten prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: upper green)</small>||[[Flakstad]], [[Moskenes]], [[Vestv\u00e5g\u00f8y]], [[V\u00e5gan]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Vester\u00e5len_prosti|'''Vester\u00e5len prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: upper blue)</small>||[[And\u00f8y]], [[B\u00f8, Nordland|B\u00f8]], [[Hadsel]], [[Sortland]], [[\u00d8ksnes]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Ofoten_prosti|'''Ofoten prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: red)</small>||[[Evenes]], [[Hamar\u00f8y]], [[L\u00f8dingen]], [[Narvik]], [[Tjeldsund]], [[Tysfjord]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Salten_prosti|'''Salten prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: upper yellow)</small>||[[Beiarn]], [[Fauske]], [[Saltdal]], [[Steigen]], [[S\u00f8rfold]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Nord-Helgeland_prosti|'''Nord-Helgeland prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: light blue)</small>||[[Alstahaug]], [[D\u00f8nna]], [[Her\u00f8y, Nordland|Her\u00f8y]], [[Leirfjord]], [[Lur\u00f8y]], [[Nesna]], [[R\u00f8d\u00f8y]], [[Tr\u00e6na]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Indre_Helgeland_prosti|'''Indre Helgeland prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: lower green)</small>||[[Grane, Nordland|Grane]], [[Hattfjelldal]], [[Hemnes]], [[Rana, Norway|Rana]], [[Vefsn]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#S\u00f8r-Helgeland_prosti|'''S\u00f8r-Helgeland prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: lower yellow)</small>||[[Bindal]], [[Br\u00f8nn\u00f8y]], [[S\u00f8mna]], [[Vega, Norway|Vega]], [[Vevelstad]]\n|}\n\n{{see also|List of churches in Nordland}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110724174820/http://www.kirken.bodo.no/wips/1288225687/ Church of Norway in Bod\u00f8 ]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110723211804/http://webster.hibo.no/kantun/bib/Katedr0.htm Bod\u00f8 Cathedral]\n\n{{Bishops of Norway}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Diocese of Sor-Haalogaland}}\n[[Category:Church of Norway dioceses|Sor-Haalogaland]]\n[[Category:Nordland]]\n[[Category:Christian organizations established in 1952]]\n[[Category:1952 establishments in Norway]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Bod\u00f8]]\n\n\n{{Norway-stub}}\n{{Lutheran-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox diocese\n|jurisdiction = Diocese\n|name         = S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland\n|local        = S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland bisped\u00f8mme\n|image        = Bod\u00f8 domkirke.jpg \n|caption      = View of Bod\u00f8 Cathedral\n|country      = [[Norway]]\n|territory    = [[Nordland]]\n|denomination = [[Church of Norway]]\n|established  = 1952\n|bishop       = [[Ann-Helen Fjeldstad Jusnes]]\n|cathedral    = [[Bod\u00f8 Cathedral]]\n|deaneries    = Bod\u00f8 domprosti, Lofoten, Ofoten, Vester\u00e5len, Salten, Nord-Helgeland, Indre Helgeland, S\u00f8r-Helgeland\n|parishes     = 96\n|members      = 198,420\t\n|map          = Dioceses Church of Norway.svg\n|map_caption  = Location of S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland diocese\n|website      = http://www.kirken.no/sor-haalogaland\n|footnotes    = Reference<ref name=\"snl\">{{cite web|url=http://snl.no/S%C3%B8r-H%C3%A5logaland_bisped%C3%B8mme|title=S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland bisped\u00f8mme|author=Store norske leksikon|authorlink=Store norske leksikon|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2011-10-28}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland''' is a [[diocese]] in the [[Church of Norway]]. The Diocese covers the Lutheran [[Church of Norway]] churches located within [[Nordland]] county in [[Norway]].  The diocese is headquartered in the [[Bod\u00f8 (town)|town of Bod\u00f8]] at [[Bod\u00f8 Cathedral]], the seat of the presiding Bishop [[Ann-Helen Fjeldstad Jusnes]] (since 2015).  The diocese is divided into eight [[deanery|deaneries]] {{lang|no|(prosti)}}.\n\n==History==\nIn 1952, the old [[Diocese of H\u00e5logaland]] (which covered all of [[Northern Norway]]) was split into two: the Diocese of S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland (Nordland county) and the [[Diocese of Nord-H\u00e5logaland]] ([[Troms]], [[Finnmark]], and [[Svalbard]]).\n\n==Bishops==\nThe bishops of S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland since its creation in 1952:\n\n*1952\u20131959: [[Wollert Krohn-Hansen]] \n*1959\u20131969: [[Hans Edvard Wisl\u00f8ff]]\n*1969\u20131982: [[Bjarne Odd Weider]] \n*1982\u20131992: [[Fredrik Gr\u00f8nnings\u00e6ter]] \n*1992\u20132006: [[\u00d8ystein Ingar Larsen]] \n*2007-2015: [[Tor Berger J\u00f8rgensen]] \n*Since 2015: [[Ann-Helen Fjeldstad Jusnes]] \n\n==Cathedral==\n{{main|Bod\u00f8 Cathedral}}\nThe old church in Bod\u00f8 was destroyed during [[World War II]], and after the war plans were made to replace the church and make it the cathedral for the new diocese. The foundation stone was laid in 1954 and was consecrated by Bishop [[Wollert Krohn-Hansen]] in 1956. There is also a memorial to those who died in Bod\u00f8 during the [[Second World War]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ub.uit.no/baser/arkinord/categories.php?cat_id=180&l=norwegian|title=Bod\u00f8 Cathedral|publisher=Arkitekturguide Nordnorge og Svalbard}}</ref>\n\n==Structure==\nThe Diocese of S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland is divided into eight [[deanery|deaneries]] ({{lang-no|prosti}}).  Each one corresponds to several municipalities in the diocese. Each municipality is further divided into one or more [[parish]]es which each contain one or more congregations. See each municipality below for lists of churches and parishes within them.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Deanery (''prosti'') !! Municipalities !! Diocese Map\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Bod\u00f8_domprosti|'''Bod\u00f8 domprosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: lower blue)</small>||[[Bod\u00f8]], [[Gildesk\u00e5l]], [[Mel\u00f8y]], [[R\u00f8st]], [[V\u00e6r\u00f8y]]||rowspan=\"8\"|[[File:Prostier i Nordland.svg|200px]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Lofoten_prosti|'''Lofoten prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: upper green)</small>||[[Flakstad]], [[Moskenes]], [[Vestv\u00e5g\u00f8y]], [[V\u00e5gan]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Vester\u00e5len_prosti|'''Vester\u00e5len prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: upper blue)</small>||[[And\u00f8y]], [[B\u00f8, Nordland|B\u00f8]], [[Hadsel]], [[Sortland]], [[\u00d8ksnes]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Ofoten_prosti|'''Ofoten prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: red)</small>||[[Ballangen]], [[Evenes]], [[Hamar\u00f8y]], [[L\u00f8dingen]], [[Narvik]], [[Tjeldsund]], [[Tysfjord]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Salten_prosti|'''Salten prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: upper yellow)</small>||[[Beiarn]], [[Fauske]], [[Saltdal]], [[Steigen]], [[S\u00f8rfold]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Nord-Helgeland_prosti|'''Nord-Helgeland prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: light blue)</small>||[[Alstahaug]], [[D\u00f8nna]], [[Her\u00f8y, Nordland|Her\u00f8y]], [[Leirfjord]], [[Lur\u00f8y]], [[Nesna]], [[R\u00f8d\u00f8y]], [[Tr\u00e6na]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#Indre_Helgeland_prosti|'''Indre Helgeland prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: lower green)</small>||[[Grane, Nordland|Grane]], [[Hattfjelldal]], [[Hemnes]], [[Rana, Norway|Rana]], [[Vefsn]]\n|-\n|[[List_of_churches_in_S\u00f8r-H\u00e5logaland#S\u00f8r-Helgeland_prosti|'''S\u00f8r-Helgeland prosti''']]<br /><small>(Map: lower yellow)</small>||[[Bindal]], [[Br\u00f8nn\u00f8y]], [[S\u00f8mna]], [[Vega, Norway|Vega]], [[Vevelstad]]\n|}\n\n{{see also|List of churches in Nordland}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110724174820/http://www.kirken.bodo.no/wips/1288225687/ Church of Norway in Bod\u00f8 ]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110723211804/http://webster.hibo.no/kantun/bib/Katedr0.htm Bod\u00f8 Cathedral]\n\n{{Bishops of Norway}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Diocese of Sor-Haalogaland}}\n[[Category:Church of Norway dioceses|Sor-Haalogaland]]\n[[Category:Nordland]]\n[[Category:Christian organizations established in 1952]]\n[[Category:1952 establishments in Norway]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Bod\u00f8]]\n\n\n{{Norway-stub}}\n{{Lutheran-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Redriv", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eStructure:deleted former municipality Ballangen", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diocese_of_S%C3%B8r-H%C3%A5logaland"}
{"title_page": "Trading Paint", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 film directed by Karzan Kader}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Trading Paint\n| image          = File:Trading Paint poster.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Karzan Kader]]\n| producer       = {{plainlist|\n* Alberto Burgue\u00f1o\n* [[Andrea Iervolino]]\n* Alexandra Klim\n* Silvio Muraglia\n}}\n| writer         = {{plainlist|\n* Gary Gerani\n* Craig R. Welch\n}}\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n* [[John Travolta]]\n* [[Michael Madsen]]\n* [[Shania Twain]]\n* [[Toby Sebastian]]\n}}\n| music          = Victor Reyes\n| cinematography = Jos\u00e9 David Montero\n| editing        = {{plainlist|\n* Alex Freitas\n* Julia Juaniz\n}}\n| studio         = {{plainlist|\n* AMBI Media Group\n* Paradox Studios\n* Elipsis Capital<ref>[http://www.elipsiscapital.com/en/trading-paint Trading Paint]</ref>\n* Raven\n* Sculptor Media\n}}\n| distributor    = {{plainlist|\n* [[Saban Capital Group|Saban Films]]\n}}\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|2|22}}\n| runtime        = 87 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English \n| budget         = \n| gross          = $18,566<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web |title=''Trading Paint'' (2019)|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/title/tt7052494 |publisher=[[Box Office Mojo]]. [[IMDb]] |accessdate=January 14, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Trading Paint''''' (also released as '''''Burning Rubber''''') is a 2019 American [[sports film|sport]] [[action film]] directed by [[Karzan Kader]], with a script co-written by Craig Welch and Gary Gerani.<ref name=\"screendaily.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.screendaily.com/news/-john-travolta-drama-trading-paint-begins-filming/5120840.article#|title=John Travolta drama 'Trading Paint' begins filming|author=|date=|website=screendaily.com|accessdate=15 August 2017}}</ref> It stars [[John Travolta]], [[Michael Madsen]], [[Shania Twain]] and [[Toby Sebastian]].<ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/shania-twain-michael-madsen-john-travolta-racing-movie-trading-paint-1202527663/|title=Shania Twain, Michael Madsen Join John Travolta\u2019s Racing Movie \u2018Trading Paint\u2019|first=Dave|last=McNary|date=15 August 2017|website=[[Variety (magazine)]]|accessdate=15 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nPrincipal photography began in August 2017 in Alabama.<ref name=\"variety\"/><ref name=\"screendaily.com\"/> The film was released on February 22, 2019 to generally negative reviews from critics.\n\n==Plot==\nSam and Cam Munroe are a father and son duo competing at the [[Talladega, Alabama|Talladega Short Track]] dirt race track. Sam is a local racing legend who now supports his son's racing in between dating divorcee Becca. Despite being a talented racer, Cam's car doesn't race well due to poor funding. Frustrated for losing the race due to engine issues, Sam's long-time rival, Linsky, offers Cam a chance to join his team with a new car. Cam decides to leave his father to join Linksy as a chance to prove his worth and win races. When Cam tells his father about his choice to join Linsky, Sam is enraged and warns that Linsky is a snake before firing his own son from the garage.\n\nFeeling down from Cam's defection, Sam spends the night drinking his woes away. By the following day, Sam decides to bring himself out of retirement and restore his status as a champion racer. While everyone thinks Sam is crazy to race so late in life, he quickly proves his experience and driving skills are still top notch and wins several races. With Sam reclaiming his title as champion racer, Linsky feels threatened by Sam and wants Cam to crash into Sam's car. Unable to crash into his father, Linsky has another racer stage a crash at the next race. Dunn causes Cam to spin out and Sam crashes into Cam's car onto the side. Although Cam survives his crash, he suffers multiple fractures on his leg and he is out of race for several months.\n\nIn between these six months of recovery, Sam and Cam make peace with each other and Sam learns about Linsky wanting Cam to crash into him. With both cars severely damaged, they need a new car to get back into racing. Throughout this time, Sam has kept the 1970 Mustang that killed his wife. Because of sentimental value, he could never sell it. However, in order to buy a new dirt Late Model for Cam to drive, which costs about $80,000, Sam decides to sell his car to Linsky. Now devoting all his energy into building the new car, the Munroe family pools their efforts into getting the car ready and supports Cam's return to the circuit.\n\nLinsky wants to beat Sam to finally prove who's the better racer; he has to settle with racing Cam instead. During the race, Linsky spins out Cam in the final two laps of the race. Cam manages to restart his car and rallies from the rear of the field over the final two laps (which is quite unlikely) and wins the race. Linsky is denied his victory as Munroe won the race. When commenting about the race with the press, Cam gives credit to Sam and his loving wife for their support. In the aftermath, the Munroes celebrate Cam's daughter's first birthday. Cam has gotten a new apartment to settle the family in and Sam solidifies his relationship with Becca, having finally found happiness and peace with his life.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[John Travolta]] as Sam Munroe\n* [[Shania Twain]] as Becca\n* [[Toby Sebastian]] as Cam Munroe\n* [[Rosabell Laurenti Sellers]] as Cindy (Cam's wife)\n* [[Michael Madsen]] as Linsky\n* [[Kevin Dunn]] as Stumpy\n* [[Buck Taylor]] as Ben\n* [[Luis Da Silva]] as Diner Redneck\n* Margaret Bowman as Martha\n* Gioia Libardoni as Kelly\n* [[Denny M\u00e9ndez]] as Dr. Deena Thompson\n* Chris Mullinax as Jack Dunn\n* [[Red Farmer]] as Ray Miller\n* Jen Baker and Faith Bruner as Track Girls\n* Jonathan Aidan Cockrell as James\n* John Flanagan as Race Car Driver\n* Haley Flanagan as Banquet Dancer\n* [[Audrey Fafard]] as Jenny Monroe\n\n==Response==\n===Box office===\n''Trading Paint'' grossed $0 in the United States and Canada<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Trading-Paint-(2019)#tab=summary |title=''Trading Paint'' (2019) - Financial Information |publisher=[[The Numbers (website)|The Numbers]], Nash Information Services, LLC |accessdate=January 14, 2020}}</ref> and $6,898 in other territories.<ref name=\"BOM\" />\n\n===Critical reception===\nOn [[review aggregator]] [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film [[List of films with a 0% rating on Rotten Tomatoes|holds a critic approval rating of 0%]] based on 12 reviews, with an [[average rating]] of 3.81/10.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/trading_paint |title=''Trading Paint'' (2019) |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]].[[Fandango (company)|Fandango Media]] |accessdate=January 14, 2020}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a weighted average score of 34 out of 100, based on 5 critics, indicating \"generally unfavorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/trading-paint |title=''Trading Paint'' Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]]. [[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=January 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n|+Awards and nominations for ''Trading Paint''\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: LightSteelBlue;\" | List of awards and nominations\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\"| Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\"| Category\n! scope=\"col\"| Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n|-\n|[[Golden Raspberry Awards]]\n|[[40th Golden Raspberry Awards|March 16, 2020]]<ref name=\"Razzies\">{{cite web|url=https://www.razzies.com/razz-newz.html|title=RAZZ NEWZ - The Razzies!|website=razzies.com}}</ref>\n|[[Golden Raspberry Award for Worst Actor|Worst Actor]]\n|[[John Travolta]] <small>(also for ''[[The Fanatic (2019 film)|The Fanatic]]'')</small>\n|{{won}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n