{"title_page": "Tengku Zulpuri Shah Raja Puji", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Malay name|Zulpuri Shah|Puji}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|honorific_prefix=[[Malay titles#Honorary styles|Yang Berhormat Mulia]]\n|name = Tengku Zulpuri Shah\n|native_name = \u062a\u06a0\u0643\u0648 \u0630\u0648\u0644\u06a4\u0648\u0631\u064a \u0634\u0627\u0647 \u0628\u0646 \u0631\u0627\u062c \u06a4\u0648\u062c\u064a\n|honorific_suffix = {{small|[[Member of Parliament|MP]]}}\n|office = [[Ministry of Water, Land and Natural Resources (Malaysia)|Deputy Minister of Water, Land and Natural Resources]]\n|termstart = 2 July 2018\n|termend = 24 February 2020\n|predecessor = [[Hamim Samuri]]\n|successor = [[Ali Biju]] {{small|as Deputy Minister of Energy and Natural Resources}}\n\n|constituency = [[Raub (federal constituency)|Raub]]\n|office1 = Vice Chairman of the [[Democratic Action Party]]\n|termstart1 = 12 November 2017\n|2blankname1 = Secretary-General\n|2namedata1 = [[Lim Guan Eng]]\n|1blankname1 = Chairman\n|1namedata1 = [[Tan Kok Wai]]\n|alongside1 = [[Kulasegaran Murugeson]]<br />[[Chow Kon Yeow]]<br />[[Chong Chieng Jen]] \n|constituency_MP2=[[Raub (federal constituency)|Raub]]\n|parliament2 = Malaysian\n|termstart2 = 9 May 2018\n|predecessor2 = [[Ariff Sabri Abdul Aziz]]\n|majority2 = 3,159 ([[2018 Malaysian general election|2018]])\n|office3 = Leader of the Opposition of the [[Pahang State Legislative Assembly]]\n|termstart3 = 5 May 2013\n|termend3 = 9 May 2018\n|constituency_AM4 = [[Mentakab (state constituency)|Mentakab]]\n|assembly4 = Pahang State Legislative\n|termstart4 = 5 May 2013\n|termend4 = 9 May 2018\n|majority4 = 1,554 ([[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]])\n|preceded4 = Chuah Boon Seong\n|succeeded4 = Woo Chee Wan\n|birth_name = Tengku Zulpuri Shah bin Raja Puji\n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1964|7|15}}\n|birth_place = [[Raub, Pahang|Raub]], [[Pahang]], [[Malaysia]]\n|title=\n|residence=[[Pahang]]\n| death_date\t\t=\n| death_place      \t=\n| resting_place         =\n|monarch=[[Muhammad V of Kelantan|Muhammad V]]<br /> [[Abdullah of Pahang|Abdullah]]\n|minister=[[Xavier Jayakumar Arulanandam]]\n|party=[[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|DAP]] (2000-present)\n|primeminister=[[Mahathir Mohamad]]\n|spouse=Rashidah Ab Rahim\n|parents=Tengku Puji Tengku Abdul Hamid\n}}\n\n'''Tengku Zulpuri Shah bin Raja Puji''' ([[Jawi alphabet|Jawi]]: \u062a\u06a0\u0643\u0648 \u0630\u0648\u0644\u06a4\u0648\u0631\u064a \u0634\u0627\u0647 \u0628\u0646 \u0631\u0627\u062c \u06a4\u0648\u062c\u064a) (born July 15, 1964) is a Malaysian politician and is currently a Vice-Chairman of the [[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|Democratic Action Party]] (DAP) since 12 November 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2017/11/12/dap-finalises-cec-lineup/|title=DAP finalises CEC lineup - Nation {{!}} The Star Online|website=www.thestar.com.my|access-date=2018-07-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718055318/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2017/11/12/dap-finalises-cec-lineup/|archive-date=18 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He also serves as Pahang DAP Deputy Chairman and is a member of the Pahang royal family.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mstar.com.my/berita/berita-semasa/2013/04/01/pru13-dap-umum-calon-negeri-pahang/|title=PRU13: DAP Umum Calon Negeri Pahang - Berita Semasa {{!}} mStar|last=MEI|first=WONG PEK|website=www.mstar.com.my|access-date=2018-07-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718114450/http://www.mstar.com.my/berita/berita-semasa/2013/04/01/pru13-dap-umum-calon-negeri-pahang/|archive-date=18 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He is the son of Tengku Puji Tengku Abdul Hamid, former Pahang [[Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]] deputy commissioner who is also a former PAS committee member. He was also appointed as Member of the [[Selayang Municipal Council]] (MPS) in Selangor in 2009.\n\nHe was sworn in as the [[Ministry of Water, Land and Natural Resources (Malaysia)|Deputy Minister of Water, Land and Natural Resources]] on 2 July 2018 in the presence of His Majesty the [[Yang di-Pertuan Agong|Yang di Pertuan Agong]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2018/07/386539/meet-malaysias-new-cabinet-26-ministers-23-deputy-ministers|title=Meet Malaysia's New Cabinet|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710133502/https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2018/07/386539/meet-malaysias-new-cabinet-26-ministers-23-deputy-ministers|archive-date=10 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nHe is the current [[Dewan Rakyat|Member of Parliament]] for [[Raub (federal constituency)|Raub]].\n\nHe was the [[Pahang State Legislative Assembly]]man for [[Mentakab (state constituency)|Mentakab]] and previously served as Opposition Leader of the Pahang State Assembly from 2013\u20132018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2013/06/30/pahang-assembly-mentakab-rep-tengku-zulpuri-shah-raja-puji-chosen-opposition-leader/|title=Pahang assembly: Mentakab rep Tengku Zulpuri Shah Raja Puji chosen Opposition leader  - Nation {{!}} The Star Online|website=www.thestar.com.my|access-date=2018-07-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718084136/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2013/06/30/pahang-assembly-mentakab-rep-tengku-zulpuri-shah-raja-puji-chosen-opposition-leader/|archive-date=18 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.freemalaysiatoday.com/category/nation/2017/11/29/follow-example-of-pahang-mb-kit-siang-tells-politicians/|title=Follow example of Pahang MB, Kit Siang tells politicians|date=2017-11-29|work=Free Malaysia Today|access-date=2018-07-18|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Election results ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ '''[[Pahang State Legislative Assembly]]'''<ref name=\"election results\">{{cite web|url=http://semak.spr.gov.my/spr/laporan/5_KedudukanAkhir.php |title=Keputusan Pilihan Raya Umum Parlimen/Dewan Undangan Negeri |publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]] |language=Malay |accessdate=4 February 2017 }} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref><ref name=\"undiinfo\">{{Cite web\n  | title = Malaysia General Election \n  | work = undiinfo Malaysian Election Data\n  | publisher = [[Malaysiakini]]\n  | url = http://undi.info/#\n  | accessdate = 4 February 2017}} Results only available from the [[2004 Malaysian general election|2004 election]].</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://resultpru13.spr.gov.my/module/keputusan/paparan/paparan_laporan.php|title=KEPUTUSAN PILIHAN RAYA UMUM 13|work=Sistem Pengurusan Maklumat Pilihan Raya Umum|publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]] |language=Malay|accessdate=24 March 2017}}</ref> \n!Year\n!Constituency\n! colspan=\"2\" |\n!Votes\n!Pct\n! colspan=\"2\" |Opponent(s)\n!Votes\n!Pct\n!Ballots cast\n!Majority\n!Turnout\n|-\n|[[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]]\n|'''N30 [[Mentakab (state constituency)|Mentakab]], P088 Temerloh'''\n|{{Party shading/Democratic Action Party}}|\n|'''Tengku Zulpuri Shah Raja Puji''' ([[Democratic Action Party|'''DAP''']])\n|'''7,882'''\n|'''55.47%'''\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|Chuah Boon Seong ([[Malaysian Chinese Association|MCA]])\n|6,328\n|44.53%\n|14,430\n|1,554\n|84.93%\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+'''[[Dewan Rakyat|Parliament of Malaysia]]'''<ref name=\"undiinfo\"/><ref name=\"GE14 results\">{{cite web|url=https://keputusan.spr.gov.my/|title=SEMAKAN KEPUTUSAN PILIHAN RAYA UMUM KE - 14|publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]] |language=Malay|accessdate=17 May 2018}} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref><ref name=\"The Star GE14\">{{cite web|url=https://election.thestar.com.my/|title=The Star Online GE14|publisher=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|accessdate=24 May 2018}} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref>   \n!Year\n!Constituency\n! colspan=\"2\" |\n!Votes\n!Pct\n! colspan=\"2\" |Opponent(s)\n!Votes\n!Pct\n!Ballots cast\n!Majority\n!Turnout\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[2018 Malaysian general election|2018]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''P80 [[Raub (federal constituency)|Raub]], Pahang'''\n| rowspan=2 {{Party shading/Keadilan}} | \n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''Tengku Zulpuri Shah Raja Puji''' ([[Democratic Action Party|'''DAP''']])\n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''20,659'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''44.89%'''\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|[[Chew Mei Fun]] ([[Malaysian Chinese Association|MCA]])\n|17,500\n|29.66%\n| rowspan=\"2\" |46,971\n| rowspan=\"2\" |3,159\n| rowspan=\"2\" |81.37%\n|-\n|{{Party shading/PAS}} |\n|Mohd Nilam Abd Manap ([[Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]])\n|7,866\n|17.09%\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Malaysian Ministers}}\n{{Pahang-FedRep}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{portal|Malaysia}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zulpuri Shah, Puji}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Pahang]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Malay descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Bugis descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian Muslims]]\n[[Category:Democratic Action Party (Malaysia) politicians]]\n[[Category:Members of the Dewan Rakyat]]\n[[Category:Members of the Pahang State Legislative Assembly]]\n[[Category:21st-century Malaysian politicians]]\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n\n\n{{Malaysia-politician-stub}}\n{{Malaysia-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Malay name|Zulpuri Shah|Puji}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|honorific_prefix=[[Malay titles#Honorary styles|Yang Berhormat Mulia]]\n|name = Tengku Zulpuri Shah\n|native_name = \u062a\u06a0\u0643\u0648 \u0630\u0648\u0644\u06a4\u0648\u0631\u064a \u0634\u0627\u0647 \u0628\u0646 \u0631\u0627\u062c \u06a4\u0648\u062c\u064a\n|honorific_suffix = {{small|[[Member of Parliament|MP]]}}\n|office = [[Ministry of Water, Land and Natural Resources (Malaysia)|Deputy Minister of Water, Land and Natural Resources]]\n|termstart = 2 July 2018\n|termend = 24 February 2020\n|predecessor = [[Hamim Samuri]]\n|successor = [[Ali Biju]] {{small|as Deputy Minister of Energy and Natural Resources}}\n\n|constituency = [[Raub (federal constituency)|Raub]]\n|office1 = Vice Chairman of the [[Democratic Action Party]]\n|termstart1 = 12 November 2017\n|2blankname1 = Secretary-General\n|2namedata1 = [[Lim Guan Eng]]\n|1blankname1 = Chairman\n|1namedata1 = [[Tan Kok Wai]]\n|alongside1 = [[Kulasegaran Murugeson]]<br />[[Chow Kon Yeow]]<br />[[Chong Chieng Jen]] \n|constituency_MP2=[[Raub (federal constituency)|Raub]]\n|parliament2 = Malaysian\n|termstart2 = 9 May 2018\n|predecessor2 = [[Ariff Sabri Abdul Aziz]]\n|majority2 = 3,159 ([[2018 Malaysian general election|2018]])\n|office3 = Leader of the Opposition of the [[Pahang State Legislative Assembly]]\n|termstart3 = 5 May 2013\n|termend3 = 9 May 2018\n|constituency_AM4 = [[Mentakab (state constituency)|Mentakab]]\n|assembly4 = Pahang State Legislative\n|termstart4 = 5 May 2013\n|termend4 = 9 May 2018\n|majority4 = 1,554 ([[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]])\n|preceded4 = Chuah Boon Seong\n|succeeded4 = Woo Chee Wan\n|birth_name = Tengku Zulpuri Shah bin Raja Puji\n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1964|7|15}}\n|birth_place = [[Raub, Pahang|Raub]], [[Pahang]], [[Malaysia]]\n|title=\n|residence=[[Pahang]]\n| death_date\t\t=\n| death_place      \t=\n| resting_place         =\n|monarch=[[Muhammad V of Kelantan|Muhammad V]]<br /> [[Abdullah of Pahang|Abdullah]]\n|minister=[[Xavier Jayakumar Arulanandam]]\n|party=[[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|DAP]] (2000-present)\n|primeminister=[[Mahathir Mohamad]]\n|spouse=Rashidah Ab Rahim\n|parents=Tengku Puji Tengku Abdul Hamid\n}}\n\n'''Tengku Zulpuri Shah bin Raja Puji''' ([[Jawi alphabet|Jawi]]: \u062a\u06a0\u0643\u0648 \u0630\u0648\u0644\u06a4\u0648\u0631\u064a \u0634\u0627\u0647 \u0628\u0646 \u0631\u0627\u062c \u06a4\u0648\u062c\u064a) (born July 15, 1964) is a Malaysian politician and is currently a Vice-Chairman of the [[Democratic Action Party (Malaysia)|Democratic Action Party]] (DAP) since 12 November 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2017/11/12/dap-finalises-cec-lineup/|title=DAP finalises CEC lineup - Nation {{!}} The Star Online|website=www.thestar.com.my|access-date=2018-07-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718055318/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2017/11/12/dap-finalises-cec-lineup/|archive-date=18 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He also serves as Pahang DAP Deputy Chairman and is a member of the Pahang royal family.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mstar.com.my/berita/berita-semasa/2013/04/01/pru13-dap-umum-calon-negeri-pahang/|title=PRU13: DAP Umum Calon Negeri Pahang - Berita Semasa {{!}} mStar|last=MEI|first=WONG PEK|website=www.mstar.com.my|access-date=2018-07-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718114450/http://www.mstar.com.my/berita/berita-semasa/2013/04/01/pru13-dap-umum-calon-negeri-pahang/|archive-date=18 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He is the son of Tengku Puji Tengku Abdul Hamid, former Pahang [[Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]] deputy commissioner who is also a former PAS committee member. He was also appointed as Member of the [[Selayang Municipal Council]] (MPS) in Selangor in 2009.\n\nHe was sworn in as the [[Ministry of Water, Land and Natural Resources (Malaysia)|Deputy Minister of Water, Land and Natural Resources]] on 2 July 2018 in the presence of His Majesty the [[Yang di-Pertuan Agong|Yang di Pertuan Agong]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2018/07/386539/meet-malaysias-new-cabinet-26-ministers-23-deputy-ministers|title=Meet Malaysia's New Cabinet|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710133502/https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2018/07/386539/meet-malaysias-new-cabinet-26-ministers-23-deputy-ministers|archive-date=10 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nHe is the current [[Dewan Rakyat|Member of Parliament]] for [[Raub (federal constituency)|Raub]].\n\nHe was the [[Pahang State Legislative Assembly]]man for [[Mentakab (state constituency)|Mentakab]] and previously served as Opposition Leader of the Pahang State Assembly from 2013\u20132018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2013/06/30/pahang-assembly-mentakab-rep-tengku-zulpuri-shah-raja-puji-chosen-opposition-leader/|title=Pahang assembly: Mentakab rep Tengku Zulpuri Shah Raja Puji chosen Opposition leader  - Nation {{!}} The Star Online|website=www.thestar.com.my|access-date=2018-07-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718084136/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2013/06/30/pahang-assembly-mentakab-rep-tengku-zulpuri-shah-raja-puji-chosen-opposition-leader/|archive-date=18 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.freemalaysiatoday.com/category/nation/2017/11/29/follow-example-of-pahang-mb-kit-siang-tells-politicians/|title=Follow example of Pahang MB, Kit Siang tells politicians|date=2017-11-29|work=Free Malaysia Today|access-date=2018-07-18|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Election results ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ '''[[Pahang State Legislative Assembly]]'''<ref name=\"election results\">{{cite web|url=http://semak.spr.gov.my/spr/laporan/5_KedudukanAkhir.php |title=Keputusan Pilihan Raya Umum Parlimen/Dewan Undangan Negeri |publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]] |language=Malay |accessdate=4 February 2017 }} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref><ref name=\"undiinfo\">{{Cite web\n  | title = Malaysia General Election \n  | work = undiinfo Malaysian Election Data\n  | publisher = [[Malaysiakini]]\n  | url = http://undi.info/#\n  | accessdate = 4 February 2017}} Results only available from the [[2004 Malaysian general election|2004 election]].</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://resultpru13.spr.gov.my/module/keputusan/paparan/paparan_laporan.php|title=KEPUTUSAN PILIHAN RAYA UMUM 13|work=Sistem Pengurusan Maklumat Pilihan Raya Umum|