pan=2|74.37%\n|-\n|{{Party shading/PAS}} |\n|Abdul Rani Osman ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]])\n|align=\"right\" |6,902\n|22.04%\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[2018 Malaysian general election|2018]]\n|rowspan=2 {{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|rowspan=2|{{nowrap|Budiman Mohd Zohdi}} ([[United Malay National Organization|UMNO]])\n|rowspan=2 align=\"right\" |16,636\n|rowspan=2|34.10%\n|{{Party shading/Keadilan}} | \n|'''Muslimin Yahaya''' ([[Malaysian United Indigenous Party|'''PPBM''']])\n|align=\"right\" |'''17,350'''\n|'''35.60%'''\n|rowspan=2|41,878\t\n|rowspan=2|714\t\n|rowspan=2|85.92%\n|-\n|{{Party shading/PAS}} |\n|Mohamed Salleh M Husin ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]])\n|align=\"right\" |7,220\n|14.80%\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zohdi, Budiman Mohd}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Selangor]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Malay descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian Muslims]]\n[[Category:United Malays National Organisation politicians]]\n[[Category:Members of the Dewan Rakyat]]\n[[Category:Members of the Selangor State Legislative Assembly]]\n[[Category:National University of Malaysia alumni]]\n[[Category:Universiti Putra Malaysia]]\n[[Category:21st-century Malaysian politicians]]\n[[Category:Medallists of the Order of the Defender of the Realm]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Malay name|Budiman|Mohd Zohdi}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix   = \n| name = Budiman Mohd Zohdi\n| honorific-suffix = \n| image = Budiman Zohdi Fullbody.jpg\n| image_size = 200px\n| caption =\n\n| constituency_MP = [[Sungai Besar]], Selangor\n| parliament      = Malaysian\n| term_start      = 18 June 2016\n| term_end        = 10 May 2018\n| majority        = 9,191 (2016)\n| predecessor     = [[Noriah Kasnon]] ([[United Malays National Organisation|UMNO]]-[[Barisan Nasional|BN]])\n| successor       = Muslimin Yahaya ([[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|PKR]]-[[Pakatan Harapan|PH]])\n\n| constituency_AM2 =  [[Sungai Panjang (state constituency)|Sungai Panjang]]\n| assembly2 = Selangor State Legislative\n| term_start2 = 5 May 2013\n| term_end2 = 10 May 2018\n| predecessor2 = [[Mohamed Khir Toyo]] ([[United Malays National Organisation|UMNO]]-[[Barisan Nasional|BN]])\n| successor2 = Mohd Imran Tamrin ([[United Malays National Organisation|UMNO]]-[[Barisan Nasional|BN]])\n| majority2 = 2,183 (2013)\n\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1972|03|11|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Sungai Besar]], [[Selangor]], [[Malaysia]]\n| residence = \n| occupation = Politician <br/>Youth activist \n| spouse =  Norma Aida Abdullah\n| children = Aida Jasmin Kirana\n| website = \n| footnotes =\n}}\n'''Budiman bin Mohd Zohdi''' (born 11 March 1972) is a [[Malaysia]]n politician. He was the [[Selangor State Legislative Assembly|Selangor state legislative assemblyman]] (ADUN) for the [[Sungai Panjang (state constituency)|Sungai Panjang]] constituency  (2013-2018) and was also the [[Parliament of Malaysia|Member of Parliament]] for the [[Sungai Besar (federal constituency)|Sungai Besar]] constituency (2016-2018) representing [[United Malay National Organization]] (UMNO), the main party in the [[Barisan Nasional]] (BN) coalition (2016-2018).\n\n==Personal life==\nBudiman lives in [[Sungai Besar]] with his wife Norma Aida Abdullah; a [[Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia]] lecturer and a daughter Aida Jasmin Kirana.\n\n==Education==\nAfter completing his Sijil Pelajaran Malaysia (Malaysian School Certificate), Budiman went to [[List of institutions using the term \"institute of technology\" or \"polytechnic\"|Polytechnic]] in [[Kota Baru]] for his Diploma in Marketing and graduated in 1992.\n\nHe then pursue his study in bachelor's degree in Business Administration at [[National University of Malaysia]] and received his scroll in 1997.\n\nFor the thirst of knowledge, he went to pursue his masters in [[University Putra Malaysia]] and graduated with the master's degree in Communication in 2003.\n\nAt present, he is a Ph.D candidate in Political Science at the [[National University of Malaysia]] since 2014.\n\nBudiman is also a Master Trainer in [[Neuro-linguistic programming]] certificate from the prestigious NFNLP USA (Dr William Horton).\n\n==Leadership==\nBudiman is a Deputy Head of UMNO for Sungai Besar division.\n\nHe was a student leader in his college years between 1992 and 1997. He leads the Mahasiswa Pro-BN movement by establishing the Tindakan Mahasiswa Bersatu team, leading to a victory in Student Council Election that year.\n\nHe won the Japan International Agency Award (JAICA) in Tokyo in 1992. His leadership skills are developed through debate and oratory. He was crowned Best Debater ASEAN University in 1996 and Malaysia Best University Debater in 1997. He is also Chairman of Jaringan Pemidato Malaysia.\n\nBudiman was appointed to foresee and lead several organization previously when BN was still the ruling government. He was also appointed as the Chairman of Board Directors for [[Malaysian Institute of Translation & Books]] (ITBM); an institute established with the aim of translating books, articles and reading materials; and publishing education books in the [[Malay language]]. In 2016, he won Anugerah Buku Negara under the entrepreneur category with a research title \"Hayati Nilai Koperasi, Semaikan Budi\".\n\nBudiman appointed to sit in Board of Directors of several government related institution such as Yayasan MARA, Cooperative College of Malaysia and Amanah Raya Berhad.\n\nHe is a writer as he has 7 books under his name, and an active contributor by writing articles for several mainstream newspaper. He is a moderator for a segment at MySuara.com (an internet radio) named Postowaibi and an active social media user.\n\n==Career==\nBudiman works for [[Telekom Malaysia]] designated as a Manager for Training and Quality, under the Group Business Assurance Team.<ref>http://www.tm.com.my/Pages/Home.aspx {{failed verification|date=March 2019}}</ref>\n\nFor his excellence performance, he was later offered a position at Federal Development Office for Selangor, under the purview of Prime Minister Office from 1 March 2012 until 1 May 2013.\n\n==NGO Involvement==\nBudiman is the founding Chairman of [[Selangor Young People Secretariat]] or Sekreteriat Orang Muda Selangor (SERANG), which is a [[Non-government organization]] (NGO) that fight for the issues of young people in Selangor<ref>{{cite news|publisher=Utusan Malaysia|author=BUDIMAN MOHD ZOHDI|work=Pengerusi Sekretariat Orang Muda Selangor (Serang)|accessdate=6 June 2016|title=Kekecewaan orang muda Selangor|date=8 June 2012|url=http://ww1.utusan.com.my/utusan/Rencana/20120608/re_06/Kekecewaan-orang-muda-Selangor|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160803204158/http://ww1.utusan.com.my/utusan/Rencana/20120608/re_06/Kekecewaan-orang-muda-Selangor|archive-date=3 August 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>  and to monitor the administration of the  state of Selangor which is led by the [[Pakatan Rakyat]].<ref>News. [https://archive.today/20130703044122/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2012/12/30/nation/12517985&sec=nation \"PKNS comes under fire\"], ''[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]'', 30 December 2012. Retrieved on 10 April 2013.</ref> They usually organize carnivals, stage performance and poem recitation in order to attract more young people to their cause.<ref>R. SITTAMPARAM. [http://www.nst.com.my/nation/general/bangi-all-set-for-carnival-1.103767 \"Bangi all set for carnival\"], ''[[New Strait Times]]'', 7 July 2012. Retrieved on 9 April 2013.</ref>\n\nSome of the issues brought forward by Budiman and his comrades are the free education promised by the state government.<ref>News. [https://archive.today/20130703044122/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2012/12/30/nation/12517985&sec=nation \"Speakers sing \u2018battle songs\u2019 for BN\u2019s victory\"], ''[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]'', 2 December 2012. Retrieved on 10 April 2013.</ref>\n\nHe is also the president of SLR Institute; a centre for social and political research.\n\nApart from that, Mr Budiman is the President of Yayasan Harapan Budi; a Foundation focusing kids and Information Technology(IT), political awareness among the physically disabled person and poverty among the youngsters.\n\nAnd Also Chairman Of Mayc Negeri Selangor And Chairman Of Majlis Belia Selangor Daerah Sabak Bernam.\n\n==Awards and recognition==\nBudiman was awarded the [[Pingat Pangkuan Negara]] (PPN), a federal medal which is awarded to those who are active in non-governmental organization.<ref>News. [https://web.archive.org/web/20100607222243/http://www.thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2010%2F6%2F6%2Fnation%2F20100606073533&sec=nation \"King's birthday honours list 2010\"], ''[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]'', Kuala Lumpur. 6 June 2013. Retrieved on 10 April 2013.</ref> Budiman also received a national youth award in 2011.\n\n==Election results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ '''[[Selangor State Legislative Assembly]]''': N03 [[Sungai Panjang]], [[Selangor]]<ref name=\"election results\">{{cite web|url=http://semak.spr.gov.my/spr/laporan/5_KedudukanAkhir.php |title=Keputusan Pilihan Raya Umum Parlimen/Dewan Undangan Negeri |publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]] | accessdate = 5 June 2016}} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://resultpru13.spr.gov.my/module/keputusan/paparan/paparan_laporan.php|title=KEPUTUSAN PILIHAN RAYA UMUM 13|work=Sistem Pengurusan Maklumat Pilihan Raya Umum|publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]]|accessdate=24 March 2017}}Results only available for the [[2013 Malaysian general election|2013 election]].</ref><ref name=\"undiinfo\">{{Cite web\n | title = Malaysia General Election \n | work = undiinfo Malaysian Election Data\n | publisher = [[Malaysiakini]]\n | url = http://undi.info/#\n | accessdate = 4 February