re said to have trained in camps in Syria before returning to Kyrgyzstan. They were reportedly planning attacks in Osh and [[Bishkek]]. Some Kyrgyz fighters that were known to be in Syria joined the Al Nusrah Front.<ref name=\"more\">{{cite web|author=Linda Lundquist |url=http://lubpak.com/archives/314433#sthash.vnvxPLti.dpuf |title=Analysis: Blowback from the Syrian jihad has begun |publisher=Lubpak.com |date=4 June 2014 |accessdate=10 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nKazakhs have joined ISIL in Syria<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=22344|title=\"Jump On A Plane & Come\" \u2013 IS Kazakhstan Jamaat Urges Kazakhs To Fight In Syria|work=From Chechnya To Syria|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=22440|title=New Video From ShamToday Shows Children In Umar Shishani's Swimming Pool|work=From Chechnya To Syria|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref> and Iraq.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=21795|title=Iraq: Claimed Images Of Kazakhstan ISIS Fighter In Ramadi|date=24 April 2014|publisher=|accessdate=27 October 2016}}</ref> ISIL released a video called \"Race Toward Good\" showing Kazakh children being trained as fighters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rferl.org/content/kazakhstan-isis-syria-recruiting/26724862.html|title=Kazakhstan Muftiate: 'Kazakh Jihadis' With IS In Syria 'Acting Against Islam'|work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref> The families of Kazakh fighters have accompanied them to Syria including children and women.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rferl.org/content/under-black-flag-kazakhstan-kazakh-women-islamic-state/26698040.html|title=Kazakhstan Intelligence: 150 Kazakh Women Are Members Of IS|work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/blogs-news-from-elsewhere-24642632|title=Kazakhstan: Video claims of 'family jihad' - BBC News|newspaper=BBC News|accessdate=25 October 2015|date=23 October 2013}}</ref> Families of Azeri and Kazakh members of ISIL have been reportedly massacred by the Syrian Islamist rebel group [[Harakat Nour al-Din al-Zenki]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=22184|title=ISIS: Syrian Brigade Massacred Families From Kazakhstan, Azerbaijan|work=From Chechnya To Syria|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref> A Kazakh fighter has appeared in [[Jaish al-Muhajireen wal-Ansar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=21351|title=Syria: A Portrait Of 3 Jaish al-Muhajireen Wal Ansar Fighters|work=From Chechnya To Syria|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref> According to the testimony of a Kazakh student who returned to Kazakhstan from Syria, the Arab Jihadist rebels in Syria were racist against the Kazakhs, assigned them the most difficult duties, and called them \"Chinese\" and there were little feelings of solidarity among the militants.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=22550|title=A Cautionary Tale: \"I Was Brainwashed Syria War Victim,\" Claims Kazakh Jihadi|work=From Chechnya To Syria|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref> A new video of ISIL Kazakh child soldiers being given military training was reported in the media.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rferl.org/content/islamic-state-children-terror-training-video/27312748.html|title='Next Generation' Stars In IS Terror-Training Video Of 'Caliphate Cub'|work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref> Kazakh passports were seized by SDF.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/arisroussinos/status/714394208371666944|title=aris roussinos on Twitter|accessdate=27 October 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328163538/https://twitter.com/arisroussinos/status/714394208371666944|archivedate=28 March 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anfenglish.com/kurdistan/relations-between-turkey-and-isis-documented-once-again#|title=ANF - Ajansa N\u00fb\u00e7eyan a Firat\u00ea|publisher=|accessdate