Islamic State |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-35036879 |accessdate=8 March 2019 |date=8 December 2015}}</ref> and the other is a Chinese-British communist named Huang Lei born in [[Sichuan Province]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Chinese-Born Militia Member Sends Selfies from Syria Frontlines - All China Women's Federation |url=http://www.womenofchina.cn/xhtml/news/newsmakers/15061305-1.htm |website=www.womenofchina.cn |accessdate=8 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Central Asia==\nIn September 2013, a Kazakh and two Kyrgyz returned from Syria and were arrested in [[Osh]] on terrorism charges on claims that they were sent to Kyrgyzstan by the [[Islamic Jihad Union]] (IJU) to perpetrate attacks. In early February 2014, six suspects were arrested in Osh, some of whom were said to have trained in camps in Syria before returning to Kyrgyzstan. They were reportedly planning attacks in Osh and [[Bishkek]]. Some Kyrgyz fighters that were known to be in Syria joined the Al Nusrah Front.<ref name=\"more\">{{cite web|author=Linda Lundquist |url=http://lubpak.com/archives/314433#sthash.vnvxPLti.dpuf |title=Analysis: Blowback from the Syrian jihad has begun |publisher=Lubpak.com |date=4 June 2014 |accessdate=10 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nKazakhs have joined ISIL in Syria<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=22344|title=\"Jump On A Plane & Come\" \u2013 IS Kazakhstan Jamaat Urges Kazakhs To Fight In Syria|work=From Chechnya To Syria|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=22440|title=New Video From ShamToday Shows Children In Umar Shishani's Swimming Pool|work=From Chechnya To Syria|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref> and Iraq.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=21795|title=Iraq: Claimed Images Of Kazakhstan ISIS Fighter In Ramadi|date=24 April 2014|publisher=|accessdate=27 October 2016}}</ref> ISIL released a video called \"Race Toward Good\" showing Kazakh children being trained as fighters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rferl.org/content/kazakhstan-isis-syria-recruiting/26724862.html|title=Kazakhstan Muftiate: 'Kazakh Jihadis' With IS In Syria 'Acting Against Islam'|work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref> The families of Kazakh fighters have accompanied them to Syria including children and women.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rferl.org/content/under-black-flag-kazakhstan-kazakh-women-islamic-state/26698040.html|title=Kazakhstan Intelligence: 150 Kazakh Women Are Members Of IS|work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/blogs-news-from-elsewhere-24642632|title=Kazakhstan: Video claims of 'family jihad' - BBC News|newspaper=BBC News|accessdate=25 October 2015|date=23 October 2013}}</ref> Families of Azeri and Kazakh members of ISIL have been reportedly massacred by the Syrian Islamist rebel group [[Harakat Nour al-Din al-Zenki]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=22184|title=ISIS: Syrian Brigade Massacred Families From Kazakhstan, Azerbaijan|work=From Chechnya To Syria|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref> A Kazakh fighter has appeared in [[Jaish al-Muhajireen wal-Ansar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=21351|title=Syria: A Portrait Of 3 Jaish al-Muhajireen Wal Ansar Fighters|work=From Chechnya To Syria|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref> According to the testimony of a Kazakh student who returned to Kazakhstan from Syria, the Arab Jihadist rebels in Syria were racist against the Kazakhs, assigned them the most difficult duties, and called them \"Chinese\" and there were little feelings of solidarity among the militants.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=22550|title=A Cautionary Tale: \"I Was Brainwashed Syria War Victim,\" Claims Kazakh Jihadi|work=From Chechnya To Syria|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref> A new video of ISIL Kazakh child soldiers being given military training was reported in the media.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rferl.org/content/islamic-state-children-terror-training-video/27312748.html|title='Next Generation' Stars In IS Terror-Training Video Of 'Caliphate Cub'|work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref> Kazakh passports were seized by SDF.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/arisroussinos/status/714394208371666944|title=aris roussinos on Twitter|accessdate=27 October 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328163538/https://twitter.com/arisroussinos/status/714394208371666944|archivedate=28 March 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anfenglish.com/kurdistan/relations-between-turkey-and-isis-documented-once-again#|title=ANF - Ajansa N\u00fb\u00e7eyan a Firat\u00ea|publisher=|accessdate=27 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011091717/https://anfenglish.com/kurdistan/relations-between-turkey-and-isis-documented-once-again|archive-date=11 October 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> The Shadadi emir was Abu Khatab al-Kazakhi.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=vvanwilgenburg|author=Wladimir|number=701301827258736640|date=21 February 2016|title=SDF captured injured Abu Khatab al-Kazakhi, IS-emir from Kazakhstan, ruled over Shadadi (source ANHA)}}</ref> Abu Aisha al-Kazakhi died in Syria.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=25055|title=Who Was Abu Aisha Kazakhi, The Kazakh IS Militant Killed In Palmyra?|work=From Chechnya To Syria|accessdate=18 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=joaska_|author=Joanna Paraszczuk|number=716995854423293952|date=4 April 2016|title=Who Was Abu Aisha Kazakhi, The Kazakh IS Militant Killed In Palmyra?}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=joaska_|author=Joanna Paraszczuk|number=715803908132700160|date=1 April 2016|title=#IS militant Abu Aisha al-Kazakhi has been killed, he went to #Syria from #Kazakhstan w his 2 kids}}</ref> Kazakh and Uzbek ISIS members invited entire families form their home countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rferl.org/content/islamic-state-central-asia-recruitment-family-affair/27653606.html|title=IS Central Asian Recruitment Drive A Family Affair|work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|accessdate=18 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=joaska_|author=Joanna Paraszczuk|number=716974196211978240|date=4 April 2016|title=How #IS Central Asian Recruitment Drive Is A Family Affair}}</ref>\n\nUzbek foreign fighters in Syria include [[Imam Bukhari Jamaat]] (\u0643\u062a\u064a\u0628\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0645\u0627\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u062e\u0627\u0631\u064a) (Uzbek: Imom al buxoriy katibasi) (Turkish: \u0130mam Buhari Cemaati),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://janlok.in/tag/katibat-al-imam-bukhari/|title=Katibat Al-Imam BukhariJanlok - Janlok|accessdate=25 October 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151024133417/http://janlok.in/tag/katibat-al-imam-bukhari/|archivedate=24 October 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=gW_zCQAAQBAJ&pg=PT84&lpg=PT84&dq=katibat+bukhari+iraq#v=onepage&q=katibat%20bukhari%20iraq&f=false|title=The Islamic State|publisher=|accessdate=25 October 2015|isbn=9789351774006|last1=Lister|first1=Charles R.|date=May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=23101|title=Uzbek Imam Bukhari Jamaat In Syria Release New Training Camp Video|date=9 December 2014|publisher=|accessdate=27 October 2016}}</ref> [[Katibat al Tawhid wal Jihad]] (\u0643\u062a\u064a\u0628\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0648\u062d\u064a\u062f \u0648\u0627\u0644\u062c\u0647\u0627\u062f) (Uzbek: Tavhid va Jihod katibasi) (Turkish: Tevhid ve Cihad Cemaati),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thelineofsteel.weebly.com/news/an-update-on-katibat-al-tawhid-wal-jihad|title=An Update on Katibat al Tawhid wal Jihad|work=The Line of Steel|accessdate=25 October 2015}} https://twitter.com/joaska_/status/759296386097672192 https://twitter.com/joaska_/status/759312091396341760 https://twitter.com/Weissenberg7/status/760212899990212608 https://twitter.com/Weissenberg7/status/760219422313156608 https://twitter.com/Weissenberg7/status/760219783228891136 https://twitter.com/Weissenberg7/status/760220004893589504 https://twitter.com/Weissenberg7/status/760214596254707712 https://twitter.com/joaska_/status/760421737221726208 https://twitter.com/joaska_/status/760422193754959872</ref> and Katibat Sayfulla (\u0643\u062a\u064a\u0628\u0629 \u0633\u064a\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647), which is part of Jabhat al-Nusra.{{better source|Twitter and blogs|date=November 2018}}\n\nUzbek Jihadist groups operate four training camps in Syria.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2015/06/over-100-jihadist-training-camps-identified-in-iraq-and-syria.php|title=Over 100 jihadist training camps identified in Iraq and Syria|work=The Long War Journal|accessdate=25 October 2015|date=21 June 2015}}</ref>\n\nKatibat al Tawhid wal Jihad (\u0422\u0430\u0432\u04b3\u0438\u0434 \u0432\u0430 \u0416\u0438\u04b3\u043e\u0434),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ozodlik.mobi/a/27450425.html|title=\u040e\u0448\u0434\u0430 \"\u0422\u0430\u0432\u04b3\u0438\u0434 \u0432\u0430 \u0416\u0438\u04b3\u043e\u0434\" \u0433\u0443\u0440\u0443\u04b3\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0433 8 \u043d\u0430\u0444\u0430\u0440 \u0430\u044a\u0437\u043e\u0441\u0438 \u0443\u0448\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0438|work=\u041e\u0437\u043e\u0434\u043b\u0438\u043a \u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e\u0441\u0438|accessdate=18 April 2016}}</ref> also called ''Jannat Oshiklari'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rferl.org/contentlive/live-blog-syria-islamic-state-isis/27363628.html?liveshare=82008#featured|title=Live Blog: Tracking Islamic State|work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|accessdate=18 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chechensinsyria.com/?p=25096|title=From South Korea to an Uzbek Al Qaeda group in Syria\u2026to a Russian prison|date=2 June 2016|publisher=|accessdate=27 October 2016}}</ref> is a largely Uzbek group active in northern Syria that was led by Abu Saloh.<ref name=Uzbekgroup>{{cite web|title=Uzbek group pledges allegiance to Al Nusrah Front|url=https://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2015/09/uzbek-group-pledges-allegiance-to-al-nusrah-front.php}}</ref> It participated in the [[2015 Northwestern Syria offensive]],<ref name=Idlibga>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A-8TznIrq-g|title=Idlibga oid so'ngi qishloqlardagi janglar - \u0418\u0434\u043b\u0438\u0431\u0433\u0430 \u043e\u0438\u0434 \u0441\u045e\u043d\u0433\u0438 \u049b\u0438\u0448\u043b\u043e\u049b\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0430\u0433\u0438 \u0436\u0430\u043d\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0440|date=31 July 2015|work=YouTube|accessdate=6 August 2015}}</ref> the [[Al-Ghab offensive (July\u2013August 2015)]],<ref name=Idlibga/><ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rlx9gHXP4Z0|title=Tel Vosit qishlog'idagi amaliyot - \u0422\u0435\u043b \u0412\u043e\u0441\u0438\u0442 \u049b\u0438\u0448\u043b\u043e\u0493\u0438\u0434\u0430\u0433\u0438 \u0430\u043c\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0451\u0442|date=5 August 2015|work=YouTube|accessdate=12 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7n74ZuNUPIo|title=Sahl al G'ob mintaqasidagi fathlari - \u0421\u0430\u04b3\u043b \u0430\u043b \u0492\u043e\u0431 \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0442\u0430\u049b\u0430\u0441\u0438\u0434\u0430\u0433\u0438 \u0444\u0430\u0442\u04b3\u043b\u0430\u0440|date=12 August 2015|work=YouTube|accessdate=12 August 2015}}</ref> [[Battle of Aleppo (2012\u2013present)]]<ref name=TLWJ>{{cite web | url= http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2015/07/al-nusrah-front-new-coalition-aleppo.php |title= Al Nusrah Front, allies form new coalition for battle in Aleppo |website= The Long War Journal |last=Joscelyn |first= Thomas|date= 3 July 2015 |accessdate= 4 July 2015 |quote= Jaysh al Fateh (\"Army of Conquest\") Qalamoun was formed in early May to fight Hezbollah, the Iranian-backed terrorist group that supports Bashar al Assad's regime, and the Islamic State.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=h